 experienced day by day across North Africa. Though some selections are drawn from published books, including memoirs, diaries, and collections of poetry, most have never been published before, nor previously translated into English. These human experiences, combined, make up the history of wartime North Africa.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aWorld War, 1939-1945vPersonal narratives, North African. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zAfrica, NorthvSources. 7aHISTORY / Africa / North.2bisacsh  aAlgeria.  aColonialism.  aFascist Italy.  aHolocaust.  aLibya.  aMorocco.  aNazi Germany.  aTunisia.  aVichy France.  aWorld War Two.1 aBoum, Aomar, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aStein, Sarah Abrevaya, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertStanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076648640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150363200440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503632004423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781503632004/original  a978-3-11-076648-6  Stanford University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles